skeleton refactor and logic for search task revival upon domain alias switch. beautiful stuff finding those object references in the object graph without introducing new parameters.
no need for these anymore as I can get them through the PerformerResultListener.
logic works out great, however UI is not reflecting the search results coming in, even if we perform the search from a task that's been added. Gotta see how the UI works now.

the search mediator is notified straight from our pong listener. The issue we have now, even creating a renewed task and getting a handle of the searchmanagerimpl is that once the onResult() event bubbles all the way up to the search mediator, it cannot find a searchresult displayer for that search token id, gotta see when it's being removed and avoid that from happening. Once I do that, i'll revert all the changes related to the DomainSwitching task as it doesn't seem necessary as cool as it was building it.
it's alive. it will perform the search again once it has a new domain alias, works beautifully.

cleanup, the PerformerResultListener didn't have to do a manager.checkIfFinished(), this wasn't letting the new attempt to search work, as it would trigger an onFinished() call in the manager, which would trigger a SearchMediator.this.onFinished(token) which would reset the SearchResultMediator token to 0, and the new search results would be orphaned.
